Rating: 3
This is so good and easier than you would think, based on the photo. I passed on this recipe when it was initially published because I didn't want to fuss with the pastry/crust/cake. However, patting the crumbs into the pan is easy and quick. I used a 9 inch pan, pushed crumbs about 3/4 of the way up the sides and it worked fine. I used about 6 peaches (mine must have been somewhat small) and berries that I froze earlier in the season - worked fine and filled the cake nicely. I have a light-colored pan and baked the full amount of time and it didn't burn or get overly brown, so don't let the posts about burned crust scare you if you have a light pan. The only change I made was to use cornstarch instead of tapioca, which I didn't have. Next time, I might use just over 1 T as the juices were thickened - almost set - but not quite set. Still, this was great and looks very professional. I'll make this again!

