Rating: 3
What a wonderful cake!! I think the problem people are having is that they are using a dark springform pan. I have a dark pan with a glass bottom and even though I took my cake out early...15 min early. My crust was too brown. If you have a dark pan decrease the oven temperature. If you have a standard pan, light coloured aluminum proceed as usual. But if you're not sure just take a peek after an hour to see how it's doing! I'll be making this again but using a different pan. Be sure to put the crust only as high as your fruit or you'll have a crown effect as some others have noted. It is a good recipe...I think Gourment should have noted what kind of pan to use, not just the size.

