Excellent taste. I used 2 T cornstarch & 2 T flour for thickening agent. I baked in convection oven at 300-325 degrees for approx. 1 hour. I also used an 8 in. springform pan and formed the dough only half way up the pan. (which makes the dough amount sufficient. If I used a larger pan, I would double the dough) The one thing I tried different from any of the other 50 reviews. (all of which were helpful) I mixed the dough in my KichenAid mixer with the paddle attachment, it worked just fine. I used peaches, blueberries and raspberries. Wonderful brunch item!

Rating: 3
This cake is unbelievably delicious. I too got worried about the temperature and cooked it at 350°, but it took longer than the time indicated in the recipe. Next time, I will cook it at 375° as recommended. We are lucky to have such beautiful peaches in BC, and this cake brings out both their flavor and that of the blueberries. I found a trick to easily flatten the dough in the cake pan: I use the bottom of a small metal measuring cup which I dip in a little flour. The dough stays cooler than if I did it with my fingers, and it is easier to achieve an even thickness.

